ar Park\n*The baroque buildings in the town's central parts\n*The Varosha architectural and historical reserve, with Drasova and Rashova memorial houses\n\n===Theatres===\n*Lovech Drama Theatre\n*Theatre by the Nauka Community Centre\n*The summer theatre in Stratesh Park\n\n===Museums===\n*Museum of Vasil Levski\n*Lovech Historical Museum\n*Drasova Memorial House\n*Rashova Memorial House\n*Saint Kliment Ohridski School\n\n==Sports==\n*[[PFC Litex Lovech]], one of Bulgaria's top football clubs\n*Osam, a men's handball club\n*Lovech '98, a women's handball club\n*Eagles, a baseball club\n*A wrestling club\n*A [[kyokushin]] [[karate]] club\n*Progress, a chess club\n*Fencing club\n\n==Notable people==\n*[[Joseph I of Bulgaria]]&nbsp;\u2014 Bulgarian exarch\n*[[Georgi Ivanov (cosmonaut)|Georgi Ivanov]]&nbsp;\u2014 the first Bulgarian cosmonaut\n*[[Dimitar Dimov]]&nbsp;\u2014 Bulgarian author\n*[[Simeon Djankov]]&nbsp;\u2014 economist\n*[[Anastas Ishirkov]]&nbsp;\u2014 noted geographer\n*[[Panayot Pipkov]]&nbsp;\u2014 composer\n\n==Partner towns==\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n*{{flagicon|ALB}} [[Berat]], Albania\n*{{flagicon|GER}} [[Erfurt]], Germany\n*{{flagicon|UKR}} [[Iziaslav, Ukraine|Iziaslav]], Ukraine\n*{{flagicon|MNE}} [[Kola\u0161in]], Montenegro\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Laval, Mayenne|Laval]], France\n*{{flagicon|RUS}} [[Lotoshino]], Russia\n*{{flagicon|RUS}} [[Ryazan]], Russia\n*{{flagicon|RUS}} [[Syktyvkar]], Russia\n*{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Valladolid]], Spain\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Honours==\n[[Lovech Heights]] in [[Graham Land]], [[Antarctica]] is named after the city,<ref>[https://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/gaz/scar/display_name.cfm?gaz_id=137473 Lovech Heights.] [[Scientific Committee on Antarctic Research|SCAR]] [[Composite Antarctic Gazetteer]].</ref> and [[Melta Point]] on [[Livingston Island]] in the [[South Shetland Islands]], [[Antarctica]] is named after the ancient Melta.<ref>[https://data.aad.gov.au/aadc/gaz/scar/display_name.cfm?gaz_id=134597 Melta Point.] [[Scientific Committee on Antarctic Research|SCAR]] [[Composite Antarctic Gazetteer]].</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Lovech-centre-imagesfrombulgaria.JPG|Central Lovech\nFile:Lovech-centre-imagesfrombulgaria2.JPG|Central Lovech\nFile:Lovech-oldtown-imagesfrombulgaria.JPG|Bulgarian National Revival quarter, ''Varosha''\nFile:Lovech-fortress-imagesfrombulgaria.JPG|The Hisarya Fortress\nFile:Bulgaria-Lovech-03.jpg|The Covered Bridge\nFile:Bulgaria-Lovech-04.jpg\nFile:Bulgaria-Lovech-05.jpg\nFile:Bulgaria-Lovech-06.jpg\nFile:Lovech.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Lovech}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110201133341/http://landmarks-bulgaria.com/lovech/ Site about Lovech in Bulgarian, English and Spanish]\n*[http://lovechtoday.com/ Lovech Today News]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20081219123947/http://www.lovechnews.com/ Lovech News] - News from Lovech\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080324234213/http://www.lovechfest.com/ Lovech Party Fest Fan Site]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070617170802/http://www.staraplanina.org/engl/lovech.php Tourist information and accommodation]\n*[http://www.guide-bulgaria.com/NC/Lovech Guide to Lovech district&nbsp;\u2014 cities, villages, resorts]\n*[http://bulgaria.domino.bg/lovetch/eng/ All about the town and the municipality of Lovech]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20050415010335/http://get.info.bg/visit/dir.asp?d=0-8-Lovech Article at Visit to Bulgaria]\n*[http://www.bulgarianproperties.com/towns-cities-villages-resorts.php?IID=59&long=Lovech+%96+The+Town+of+the+Lilacs A large article about Lovech with many pictures at BulgarianProperties.com]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n*[http://www.pbase.com/ngruev/lovetch Pictures from Lovech]\n*[http://www.ezikovata.eu Ezikovata&nbsp;\u2014 the oldest foreign language school in Bulgaria, unofficial web site]\n* [https://archive.today/20080408043441/http://gradlovech.hit.bg/ Unoffic